narr:SolutionArchetype_QAOnboarding a narr:SolutionArchetype ;
    skos:broader narr:SolutionArchetypes ;

    narr:ArchetypeTitle "QA Onboarding — Zero-Context Test Plan Development" ;
    narr:ProblemContext "Lead QA engineer transitioning from another project mid-February needs to develop test plans for bulk mail feature with zero prior context. Traditional onboarding requires weeks of meetings and document review." ;
    narr:ApproachPattern "Seed collective memory with bulk mail architecture, design decisions, and plan documents. QA engineer queries AI to understand feature, collaborates on test plan development. AI surfaces knowledge gaps when it doesn't know." ;
    narr:RequiredCapabilities "MCP server integration, bulk document ingestion (60 markdown files), knowledge gap workflow, query interface" ;
    narr:OutcomesProof "QA engineer develops comprehensive test plans without direct handoff meetings. Time-to-productivity measured in days vs. weeks." ;
    narr:TimeToValue "Mid-February 2026 (imminent timeline)" ;
    skos:note "the customer's chief architect identified this as 'the killer sales demo' — concrete, measurable, imminent. Strongest internal validation scenario." ;
    skos:related narr:Flows, narr:CaseStudies ;
    prov:wasGeneratedBy narr:Tx_20260211T012534Z .

narr:SolutionArchetype_CEOKnowledgeTransfer a narr:SolutionArchetype ;
    skos:broader narr:SolutionArchetypes ;

    narr:ArchetypeTitle "CEO Knowledge Transfer Test" ;
    narr:ProblemContext "CEO has not been involved in bulk mail design process. Needs to understand feature for strategic decisions without consuming architect time." ;
    narr:ApproachPattern "Seed collective memory with bulk mail content. Give CEO MCP URL and prompt to ask questions about bulk mail. Measure quality of answers vs. direct briefing." ;
    narr:OutcomesProof "CEO gains working knowledge of feature without meetings. Validates knowledge transfer fidelity." ;
    skos:related narr:Flows, narr:ActorIncentiveAnalysis ;
    prov:wasGeneratedBy narr:Tx_20260211T012534Z .

narr:SolutionArchetype_CodeQualityThroughContext a narr:SolutionArchetype ;
    skos:broader narr:SolutionArchetypes ;

    narr:ArchetypeTitle "Code Quality Through Business Context" ;
    narr:ProblemContext "AI coding agents (Opus) lack business context and domain knowledge, leading to hallucinated behavior and incorrect implementations when bug tickets lack clear expected behavior." ;
    narr:ApproachPattern "Enrich collective memory with business context, domain rules, and expected behavior patterns. Coding agents query collective memory during code generation. Steering becomes collaborative across team." ;
    narr:OutcomesProof "Improved code quality, reduced hallucination, collaborative steering of coding agents. Change to organizational memory agreed by CTO now changes intern's cloud agent code." ;
    skos:note "Scarlet's insight: 'not only does it do a better job writing the code, it also means that the steering of your coding agents is now collaborative.'" ;
    skos:related narr:Behaviors, narr:TechnicalExplainers ;
    prov:wasGeneratedBy narr:Tx_20260211T012534Z .

